						<summary>

						<p>This inscription, which is damaged, records the death of a hero named <hi rend="bold">Leṅka Kēta,</hi> who fell in a battle at the fort of <hi rend="bold">Ūṇukallu</hi> (the modern Uṇkal) where he fought at the command of <hi rend="bold">Sattiga</hi> (probably king <hi rend="bold">Iṟivabeḍaṅga Satyāśraya</hi>). </p>						

						<p>The date, <hi rend="bold">Śaka 9[2]7, Viśvāvasu, Phālguṇa, amāvāsyā, Sunday</hi> (according to the <hi rend="italic">Ephemeris,</hi> mistake for Saturday) corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1006, March 2, Saturday.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
